  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Evacuation Management for Local Authorities and Communities (Vanuatu) [Sef Ples Blong Yumi]</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this project is to support the Government of Vanuatu to implement key recovery priorities relating to disaster preparedness and evacuation procedures identified in the Vanuatu Recovery Strategy 2020-2023, contributing to the protection and resilience of people at risk of displacement in Vanuatu.  While traditional resilience in Vanuatu is strong, emergency preparedness needs strengthening at all levels - national, provincial, area council and community - as re-affirmed by the recent Tropical Cyclone Harold experience. IOM is co-leading the Displacement and Evacuations Centre Management Cluster and is working with key partners on disaster preparedness. Sef Ples Blong Yumi is building on these activities and relationships to build capacity of government, communities, Community Disaster and Climate Change Committees (CDCCCs) and faith-based groups, especially women leaders, to develop and maintain safe, dignified evacuation options in emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
